item.title: Shower Thoughts
item.dc:creator: Rielly1240
item.content:encoded:
The Paradox of the Shower Temperature

In the eternal battle between hot and cold, why is it that the shower always seems to betray us at the most inconvenient moments? One minute, it's a blissful cascade of warmth; the next, an icy torrent that sends shivers down our spine. Is it a test of resilience or simply the whims of fate?

item.title: Chasing the Dream
item.dc:creator: Rielly1240
item.content:encoded:
Ontario to British Columbia

Pursuing Rugby Dreams and Career Opportunities in British Columbia

As I stand on the threshold of graduation from Georgian College, a new chapter beckons—one filled with adventure, ambition, and the pursuit of dreams. My heart is set on a journey that will take me from the heart of Ontario to the rugged beauty of British Columbia, where I aim to chase my passion for rugby while seizing career opportunities in the vibrant city of Vancouver. For as long as I can remember, rugby has been more than just a sport to me. it's a way of life, a passion that fuels my spirit and ignites my soul. With every scrum, every tackle, and every try, I find myself drawn deeper into the world of rugby, captivated by its intensity, camaraderie, and unwavering spirit. My dream is to play rugby internationally for Team Canada. Step one is to be seen by Team Canada Coaches. There is nowhere better to do that than by playing in the league they are already watching, the B.C Premier League.  The B.C  Premier League, where the finest rugby talent in Canada converges to compete at the highest level. It's a challenge that fills me with excitement and anticipation, knowing that every match, every training session, brings me one step closer to realizing my dream of playing professional rugby. I am well aware that it is a massive risk to pack up all of my things fresh out of college and move to the province with one of the highest rental prices. It just so happens that most of the teams in the premier league are located in and around Victoria. Victoria BC is also a great place for me to take my knowledge in web development. According to the official BC website, there are currently 5,000 job openings for Web Designers and Developers.

item.title: What I am Learning
item.dc:creator: Rielly1240
item.content:encoded:
Reflection from the midway point

I'm halfway through my IMDW diploma at Georgian College, and so far I have had times when I was so proud of the things that I have created and I have had times where my code isn't working, and if it wasn't for my girlfriend calming me down there would be a whole in my monitor about the size of my fist. Out of everything that I have learned my two favorite subjects this far would be php, and javaScript.
